Same exact Shock and strut settings...same exact Launch Rpm and boost. Only difference is moving from 125/10 coil over mounted springs to 150/12 over axle mounted springs with #UPRproducts adjustable spring perches. 

For every 100lbs X 10lbs of unsprung weight your car has should give you your spring rate mine was 1500lbs so 150's.. obviously it's not EXACT but it's a damn good gauge to go by. My car unsprung weight (meaning not including rear end, wheels, brakes etc) is 15xx lbs. 

Small details make a huge difference. 1st pic very little separation and the car eventually spun. 2nd pic nice separation and car made a solid 1.25 60' hit.
Big changes and  A LOT of weight loss coming for 2024 on the GT500. Time to get busy.......
